Subject: Re: [T2] 69 Transporter backfires when I downshift

A less restrictive exhaust than stock, or an exhaust leak, also check your
timing. A sticking advance unit or broken spring in the advance unit will make
it stay too far advanced when getting off the throttle. Easy enough to check
if you have a strobe timing light.
